RestServiceSpringMVCJson
-----------------------------
PreRequisite: Docker Installed, Kubernetes Installed, Minikube Installed and DockerHub Account
1.From the command Line move to RestServiceSpringMVCJson directory and build the Project
2.Build Command: mvn clean install -Dwtpversion=2.0
3.from RestServiceSpringMVCJson Directory run the below commands
4.Start Minikube Command: minikube start
5.Commandline Docker login Command : docker login
Provide Username and Password  as Prompted
6.Build the image using Dockerfile
from RestServiceSpringMVCJson Directory run the command below.
docker build -t restservice .
7.Using Docker Hub and Public Repository details tag the Image
docker tag restservice:latest yourdockerhubusername/publicrepositoryname:restservice
8. Push the  image to DockerHub public repository
docker push  yourdockerhubusername/publicrepositoryname:restservice
9.Now apply the deployment : kubectl apply -f deployment.yaml
10.Now expose and Run the restservice:kubectl apply -f service.yaml
11.To know the Service Endpoint: minikube service restservice --url
12.Check the REST API with REST Client
Example1:http://192.168.99.120:31000/RestServiceSpringMVCJson/change/optimal?pence=576
Example2:http://192.168.99.120:31000/RestServiceSpringMVCJson/change/supply?pence=2000
13.Source Java8